as appropriate when you're listening to a
track as when you're looking

00:42:38.880 --> 00:42:39.880
at list of tracks.

00:42:39.880 --> 00:42:41.319
&gt;&gt;Adam: And we do have one of your favorite
actions--[unintelligible]

00:42:41.319 --> 00:42:43.000
&gt;&gt;Reto: Exit button.

00:42:43.000 --> 00:42:44.000
Yay!

00:42:44.000 --> 00:42:45.000
NO!

00:42:45.000 --> 00:42:46.190
There's no need for an exit button.

00:42:46.190 --> 00:42:50.980
For a music playing app, as soon as you are
paused, that should be the equivalent of everything

00:42:50.980 --> 00:42:52.960
stopping, there shouldn't be any services
running, there

00:42:52.960 --> 00:42:58.359
shouldn't be any difference at that point
between hitting exit or just hitting back.

00:42:58.359 --> 00:43:01.170
That should be equivalent, so
then there's no need to put it in there because,

00:43:01.170 --> 00:43:04.450
again, as soon as you have an exit button--I
understand that some

00:43:04.450 --> 00:43:09.420
users like an exit button and it's a nice
thing to put in there but it's totally ambiguous.

00:43:09.420 --> 00:43:10.420
It's meaningless.

00:43:10.420 --> 00:43:14.440
You don't--no one actually knows what that
exit button is going to do--so putting it

00:43:14.440 --> 00:43:17.530
there just runs the risk of
frustrating your users and annoying the hell

00:43:17.530 --> 00:43:18.530
out of me.

00:43:18.530 --> 00:43:19.940
Let's go back in here.

00:43:19.940 --> 00:43:20.940
