00:43:38.520 --> 00:43:39.530
I think that that gets points.

00:43:39.530 --> 00:43:40.530
&gt;&gt;Reto: Yeah, I think so.

00:43:40.530 --> 00:43:44.750
I think the first time you load, you want
to have something and we have sort of preferences

00:43:44.750 --> 00:43:48.569
around how much time you should be showing
a blank screen, i.e. no time.

00:43:48.569 --> 00:43:52.700
So definitely having a splash screen or
loading screen the first time is nice, but

00:43:52.700 --> 00:43:54.930
everything after the first time, I feel like
you should already have that

00:43:54.930 --> 00:43:57.710
data cached in a way that you can bring stuff
up quickly.

